Surulere Local Government Area (SLGA) of Lagos State on Thursday commenced the measles vaccination campaign, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. A NAN correspondent who monitored activities in the area reports that health workers were in their uniforms going from house to house to immunise children against the disease. Some of the health workers were also at schools in the area administering the measles vaccine to children within the ages required for the programme. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.